column5: Where can I get a map for Lac Suel, can I buy one from a sport shop in Ear Falls or is there a web site that I can print a map from. Thanks..............
Four Seasons used to carry them, I believe they are for four (4) sections of the lake. p.s. They don't have all the rockpiles marked!

Don't know how quickly you need one, but if you have a week or two then canadamapsales.com has nice ones. Both color and b&w.

The ontario Ministry of Natural Resouces have a number of maps in PDF format. The maps print out about 30 inches wide. The map number 930500 is the main part of the lake. Here is a link:http://crownlanduseatlas.mnr.gov.on.ca/htmls/C2317.html Ken
